The first half of the course is dedicated to the issues of linguistic study of French language, different tools of syntactic and semantic analysis will be introduced.
The second part of the course is related to the study of the French vocabulary. The course introduces the basic notions in the field of lexicology and also the basic elements of the history of lexicology and lexicography. The course gives the students an overview of the organization and the logic of vocabulary and introduces the main tools for the analysis of vocabulary.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give an overview of the main tools of French linguistic analysis. To provide with linguistic and methodological basis for individual research on a subject related to the French language.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student: 1) can identify different linguistic elements in a French language corpus and to classify them according to their function;  2) has the knowledge of French linguistic terminology and can use it correctly in linguistic analysis;    3) has an overview of the main historical periods and of recent developments of French linguistics.
